  "text": "The Longo et al. article [CITATION_1] contains a carefully executed and controlled analysis of the distribution of different kinds of repetitive elements in selected segments from three kinds of genomic region in the tammar wallaby: centromeric regions, breakpoint regions (actually three locations in one breakpoint region) and euchromatic regions not containing a breakpoint. They showed a dramatic enrichment in the breakpoint region of sequence characteristic of endogenous retroviruses (ERVs) and LINE1 transposable elements, and a deficiency of SINE",
